Enclosing interface:
DynamicContentHandler
public static interface DynamicContentHandler.ResultReceiver

A content handler result receiver is an object that expects a notification once the content handler is done. It's almost like an observer or action listener, but the only action that we make available is when the content handler is done handling content.

When a content handler is registered with an XMLReader, and the previous content handler is a result receiver, that previous content handler will be notified of the result of this content handler.
